messages.message:
Does anyone know what this cryptic mypy error is? It showed up in my failed jenkins CI (https://jenkins.instabase.com/blue/organizations/jenkins/instabase/detail/PR-35748/10/pipeline) for my PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/35748)
```[2023-01-31T22:46:24.379Z] TYPECHECKING FAILURE: mypy exited with code 1

[2023-01-31T22:46:24.379Z] /instabase_dir/shared-utils/py-utils/typing-utils/src/py/stubs/cryptography/hazmat/primitives/serialization/pkcs12.pyi:3: error: Function is missing a return type annotation

[2023-01-31T22:46:24.379Z] /instabase_dir/shared-utils/py-utils/typing-utils/src/py/stubs/cryptography/hazmat/primitives/serialization/pkcs12.pyi:3: error: Function is missing a type annotation for one or more arguments

[2023-01-31T22:46:24.379Z] Found 2 errors in 1 file (checked 55 source files)```
That `pyi` file hasn’t been touched since early 2020… :thinking_face:  Do we not ignore these pyi files in mypy checks?
but this is in the jenkins CI build though?
oh sorry, didn’t read carefully! New suggestion, check if someone upgraded the library recently? :slightly_smiling_face:
hmm, looks like it was updated 30th dec as part of the api-server-apps poetry migration, but let me check more carefully
I don't think this stub is used anywhere, you can probably just remove it?
